    "design_coherence": {
      "evidence": [
        "`chopsvc/service.go` and `handler/urbit.go` each implement an almost identical readiness waiter loop (poll status, short sleep/ticker, timeout bound, string-based Up-state check), creating duplicated lifecycle control logic across services.",
        "`handler/support.go` combines input handling, diagnostics gathering, sanitization, archive creation, and transport dispatch in one handler path, increasing coupling and reducing replacement options for each concern.",
        "Lifecycle orchestration in handlers (`handler/handler.go`, `handler/urbit_operations.go`) interleaves action parsing, transition publishing, asynchronous execution, and error handling boilerplate instead of separating orchestration policy from transport and domain operations.",
        "`docker/docker.go` includes runtime side effects (container deletion) in a configuration construction path, which leaks operational behavior into what should be a pure builder function."
      ],
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "confidence": "high"
    }
  },
  "findings": [
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-wait-loop-duplication",
      "summary": "Container readiness polling is duplicated in separate packages instead of being a shared operation policy.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/chopsvc/service.go",
        "goseg/handler/urbit.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "Both files define local wait/retry logic for operation completion with the same practical shape: repeated timed polls, fixed short polling interval, deadline-based abort, and string containment checks on reported state."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce a shared lifecycle wait utility (or policy struct) in one package and use it from both packages, exposing options for timeout and expected terminal states so callers share one consistent contract.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "shared-lifecycle-policy-gaps"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-support-handler-cohesion-break",
      "summary": "Support path handler mixes request-facing concerns with operational, filesystem, and transport concerns.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/handler/support.go",
        "goseg/handler/handler.go",
        "goseg/leak/handler.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`SupportHandler` and adjacent routing code handle inbound action parsing/dispatch while also invoking file/system collection, packaging, and outbound notification/upload behavior, creating high coupling for a single endpoint.",
        "The same file set shows little separation between policy decisions (what to gather), mechanics (how to gather/zip), and side effects (sending payloads), making future extension difficult without touching broad slices of the handler stack."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Split support into a dedicated coordinator plus pluggable collectors and an uploader interface; keep handler code responsible only for authorization/validation and routing to a domain service.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "architectural_change",
      "root_cause_cluster": "mixed-responsibility-endpoints"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-ship-handler-orchestration-blowout",
      "summary": "Ship action handling entangles parsing, validation, async orchestration, and state-transition publication in one function body.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/handler/handler.go",
        "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`NewShipHandler` performs request routing and action dispatch while embedding operation selection, transition state updates, goroutine orchestration, and repetitive inline error response behavior.",
        "Operation-specific behavior is still partly implemented via shared handler-local control flow rather than a composable transition executor, increasing accidental drift between cases."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Introduce an explicit command/transition executor abstraction (input DTO -> validated transition -> operation step list -> completion handler) and move per-operation policy out of the switch body.",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "mixed-responsibility-endpoints"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-config-builder-side-effects",
      "summary": "Container configuration helper performs destructive runtime actions, violating separation of configuration vs execution concerns.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/docker/docker.go",
        "goseg/handler/urbit_operations.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`containerConfigForType` in docker layer includes explicit container deletion calls while naming and call sites imply a pure config construction helper.",
        "This increases surprise for callers that treat the helper as a read/derive step and makes operation order/dependency harder to reason about."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Make config helpers side-effect free (build structs only) and relocate teardown/replacement actions to explicit orchestration layer with clear naming (`EnsureContainerState`, `PruneExistingContainer`).",
      "confidence": "high",
      "impact_scope": "module",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "impure-factory-patterns"
    },
    {
      "dimension": "design_coherence",
      "identifier": "dc-non-idempotent-fstab-update",
      "summary": "Filesystem bootstrap logic rewrites OS mount configuration in an append-only, non-idempotent style with weak error finalization checks.",
      "related_files": [
        "goseg/system/disk.go",
        "goseg/system/system.go"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "`CreateGroundSegFilesystem` appends GroundSeg mount lines to `/etc/fstab` without deduplication/guards and has resource-finalization patterns that do not consistently surface flush/commit failures before returning.",
        "A restart/re-run path can duplicate entries and make troubleshooting mount state brittle."
      ],
      "suggestion": "Centralize mount-entry persistence in a dedicated idempotent subsystem that detects existing equivalent entries, writes via a single atomic update, and validates fs table integrity after commit.",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "impact_scope": "subsystem",
      "fix_scope": "multi_file_refactor",
      "root_cause_cluster": "impure-initialization-logic"
    }
  ],
  "retrospective": {
    "root_causes": [
      "Shared lifecycle orchestration logic is duplicated instead of shared via explicit policy/executor abstractions.",
      "Handlers and operational helpers frequently combine parsing, decision, side-effect execution, and reporting in single paths.",
      "Pure helper layers are blurred by hidden mutation, especially around container configuration and low-level system bootstrap."
